  "name": "14-no-millis-stamp-inverts-lww",
  "description": "KNOWN BUG (И-4). Stamps are compared as STRINGS. A stamp whose zero millisecond field is omitted ('...:00Z' — what Kotlin's Instant.toString() emits) sorts AFTER every stamp in the same second that carries millis, because 'Z' (0x5A) > '.' (0x2E). Here the incoming row is chronologically 1ms OLDER, and it wins anyway. A second writer MUST always emit three-digit millis.",
